    <text>
        <body><div type="bibliography">
                
                <p><bibl><ptr target="#marengo2010a"/>, p. 155, n. <citedRange>33</citedRange>, fig. 6.33</bibl>, whence
                    <bibl><ptr target="#SEG"/>, <citedRange>60.1841.9</citedRange></bibl>;
                    <bibl><ptr target="#IGCyr"/> <citedRange>113500</citedRange></bibl>.</p>
            </div><div type="edition" xml:lang="grc" xml:space="preserve">
                
                <ab>
                    <lb n="1"/><persName type="attested" key=""><name nymRef="#Πειθαγόρας"><supplied reason="lost">Πε</supplied>ιθαγόρας</name></persName>
                </ab></div><div type="apparatus" xml:space="preserve">
            
                <p/>
               </div><div type="translation" xml:space="preserve" xml:lang="fr">
            <p>Peithagoras.</p>
         </div><div type="translation" xml:space="preserve" xml:lang="en">
            <p>Peithagoras.</p>
         </div><div type="translation" xml:space="preserve" xml:lang="it">
            <p>Peithagoras.</p>
         </div><div type="commentary">
                
                <p>Although the fragment is too small to allow a ceramological datation, its inventory number shows its provenance from a sounding in the area 
                    of the retaining wall on which the hestiatorion of the first half of the fifth century (see <bibl><ptr target="#bacchielli1981"/>, pp.
                <citedRange>43-50</citedRange></bibl>) was built. That fits the lettering well.</p>
                <p>The personal name may be that of a dedicant; anyway, the sherd is surely not an ostrakon like <ref type="inscription" source="#IGCyr2">IGCyr081900</ref>, 
                    <ref type="inscription" source="#IGCyr2">IGCyr082000</ref>, <ref type="inscription" source="#IGCyr2">IGCyr082100</ref>
                 and <ref type="inscription" source="#IGCyr2">IGCyr082200</ref> (see the discussion at <bibl><ptr target="#marengo2010a"/>, pp. <citedRange>140-144</citedRange></bibl>).</p>
            </div></body>
